organic_results.title: Basic attainment processes: A replication and extension
organic_results.snippet: Longitudinal survey data on a national sample of youth, first sampled as high-school sophomores in 1955 and followed up in 1970, were employed in a replication and extension of the Blau and Duncan" basic model" of the status attainment process. Most of the analysis was consistent with previous inquiries in this area, while the" discrepancies" suggest possible changes in status dynamics over time and the need to qualify the interpretation of such analyses with reference to" substantively relevant" characteristics of the samples …
